label.value: increased level of amino acid transport gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more amino acid transport RNAs measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells). Amino acid transport RNAs are transcribed from genes whose products are involved in amino acid transport.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-proline measured in the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-valine measured in the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-lysine measured in the cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-alanine measured in the cell is lower than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of L-asparagine measured in the cell is lower than normal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of sulfate ions into the cell is abnormal.
A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the import of sulfate ions into the cell occurs to a lower extent than normal.

label.value: abolished cell population growth on methionine sulfur source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which a cell population does not grow in a medium containing L-methionine as the sole sulfur source.

definition.value: Use this term for a population of cells that does not grow with methionine as the sulfur source, but does grow using a different sulfur source (a cell population that does not grow on any media would be considered inviable). Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise. Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: abolished cell population growth on sulfate sulfur source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which a cell population does not grow in a medium containing sulfate ions as the sole sulfur source.

definition.value: Use this term for a population of cells that does not grow with sulfate as the sulfur source, but does grow using a different sulfur source (a cell population that does not grow on any media would be considered inviable). Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise. Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise. Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of cysteine synthase activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of cysteine synthase activity is decreased.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of cysteine synthase activity is increased.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of quinidine than normal.

An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of 4-nitroquinoline N-oxide than normal.

label.value: abolished protein localization to pre-autophagosomal structure

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the pre-autophagosomal structure is abolished.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells form cytoplasmic microtubules that are shorter than normal.
A cellular process phenotype in which microtubule bundle formation, which normally results in a parallel arrangement of microtubules, is abnormal.

label.value: inviable after spore germination, without cell division, spheroid cell

value.value: A phenotype in which a spore germinates to produce an inviable cell that does not divide, and that is shaped in the form of a spheroid. In spheroid cells, there is much less difference between the long and short axes of the cell than in wild type.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of tRNA (guanine(9)-N(1))-methyltransferase activity is abnormal.
A molecular function phenotype in which tRNA (guanine(9)-N(1))-methyltransferase activity is absent.
A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of tRNA (guanine(9)-N(1))-methyltransferase activity is decreased.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of clotrimazole than normal.
An increased chemical resistance phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells grow in the presence of a higher concentration of terbinafine than normal.

label.value: decreased protein ubiquitination during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of ubiquitination of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the spindle pole body is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the spindle pole body and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the spindle pole body is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to meiotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the meiotic spindle pole body is abnormal.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found at the spindle pole body and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to meiotic spindle pole body

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the meiotic spindle pole body is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term. Use this term for cells in which in which the re-accumulation of some spindle pole body components does not occur at the onset of meiosis I.

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which a cell undergoes an abnormal nuclear division after meiosis II is complete.

label.value: increased level of ubiquitinated protein in cell during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of ubiquitinated protein measured in the cell is higher than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

definition.value: Consider also annotating to 'increased protein ubiquitination' (FYPO:0002082) if the experiment directly assays the ubiquitination reaction(s).

label.value: decreased level of sumoylated protein in cell

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of sumoylated protein measured the cell is lower than normal when the cell is in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle. Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

label.value: normal level of sumoylated protein in cell

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of sumoylated protein measured in a cell is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total protein or a specific protein may be affected.

label.value: abnormal protein sumoylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the sumoylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is abnormal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein sumoylation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the occurrence of sumoylation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites, is decreased.

label.value: abolished protein localization to nucleus, with protein mislocalized to cytoplasm, during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is abolished, and the protein is present in the cytoplasm instead.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased cellular reactive oxygen species level during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of reactive oxygen species (ROS) measured in a cell is lower than normal in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle.

label.value: increased transcription during cellular response to nitric oxide

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription occurs to a greater extent than normal during a cellular response to nitric oxide. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: increased transcription during cellular response to salt stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription occurs to a greater extent than normal during a cellular response to a salt stress. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: decreased transcription during cellular response to nitric oxide

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription occurs to a lower extent than normal during a cellular response to nitric oxide. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: decreased transcription during cellular response to salt stress

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which transcription occurs to a lower extent than normal during a cellular response to a salt stress. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

A molecular function phenotype in which riboflavin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant does not occur. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

A molecular function phenotype in which occurrence of riboflavin binding by a gene product (usually a protein) in a mutant is decreased. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.
A cell phenotype in which vacuoles are smaller than normal.
A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which vacuoles are smaller than normal.
A cell phenotype observed when the population in which the cell is found is in stationary phase in which vacuoles are smaller than normal.
A physical cellular phenotype in which cells contain more vacuoles than normal.

label.value: small vacuoles present in increased numbers during stationary phase

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a cell contains more, but smaller, vacuoles than normal when the population in which the cell is found is in stationary phase.

label.value: small vacuoles present in increased numbers during cellular hypotonic response

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell contains more, but smaller, vacuoles than normal during a cellular response to a hypotonic environment.

label.value: vacuoles present in decreased numbers during vegetative growth

value.value: A physical cellular phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells contain fewer vacuoles than normal.
